{
  "text": "We use the notation from [CITATION_1] to denote E 1,1 = supp(q 1 ) \u2229 supp(q 2 ), E 1,0 = supp(q 1 )\\supp(q 2 ), E 0,1 = supp(q 2 )\\supp(q 1 ), E 1,? = supp(q 1 ) \u2229 missing(q 2 ), E ?,1 = missing(q 1 ) \u2229 supp(q 2 ), where R = (q 1 , q 2 ) and missing(q) represents a set of elements for which we can not determine if they are in support of q due to missing values.",
